newsitem.title: CHILE: Chile reports $248 million November trade deficit. [CORRECTED 12:15 GMT]
newsitem.headline: Chile reports $248 million November trade deficit. [CORRECTED 12:15 GMT]

text.p: (Corrects deficit figure in headline and first paragraph from $240 million.)
Chile reported a trade deficit of $248 million last month compared with a $73.5 million surplus in the same month last year, said the Central Bank.
Exports fell last month to $1.18 billion in November from $1.36 billion in the same month 1995, said the Bank in its fortnightly report.
Imports rose to $1.42 billion from $1.29 billion in November 1995.
